    <learning>
      <learningContent>
        <title>Introduction</title>
        <lcInstruction>
          <description>
            <para>
					  A bike's brake system is used to slow down and stop the bike. Because of its association with rider safety, the brake system is considered to be one of a bike's more important systems.
				  </para>
            <para>
					  The type of bike you ride and how it is used will determine the type of brake system that is installed. Types of brake systems include, but are not limited to:
				  </para>
            <figure>
              <title />
              <graphic infoEntityIdent="ICN-S1000DBIKE-AAA-DA10000-A-06RT9-00125-A-001-01" />
            </figure>
            <para>Cantilever brakes are the most common on modern bikes. Therefore, this training will focus on the cantilever brake system.</para>
            <para>This topic provides information related to the physical description of a bike's brake system.</para>
            <para>
              <emphasis>Objective: Given photographs of a bike's brake system, you will be able to identify each part with 80 percent accuracy.
				  </emphasis>
            </para>
          </description>
        </lcInstruction>
      </learningContent>
    </learning>
